	<title>Non-Keyboard Characters</title>
	<para>There are four ways to add characters that are not on your keyboard to static text
	fields:</para>
	<orderedlist spacing='compact'>
		<listitem>
			<para>Keyboard entry of extended ASCII codes.</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Keyboard entry of Unicode character codes.</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Selecting characters using the Character Map utility.</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Using the AllChars program to enter characters.</para>
		</listitem>
	</orderedlist>
	<para>Each of these methods is discussed below.</para>
	<caution>
		<para>A character can only be displayed or printed if it is included in the character
		set for the selected font face. If the character is not included, then either no
		character is displayed or printed, or another character is substituted. For example,
		the font face used for the body of this manual substitutes the character '#' for
		any characters that are not included in its character set.</para>
	</caution>
